 {"id":"brenner_bot-thzu","title":"Tutorial Infrastructure: Component Library & Data Layer","description":"# Purpose

Build the foundational component library and data structures that all tutorial paths depend on. This is the shared infrastructure — get it right, and the content work becomes straightforward.

---

# Background & Rationale

## Why a Component Library First?

The ACFS wizard succeeds because it has consistent, reusable components:
- Every step looks the same (predictable UX)
- Code blocks all have copy functionality
- Collapsibles work identically everywhere
- Progress tracking is centralized

We need the same for BrennerBot's tutorial. Building components first means:
1. Content authors can focus on content, not styling
2. Consistency is enforced by architecture
3. Future maintenance is centralized

## Alignment with Existing Design System

We already have excellent components in brennerbot.org:
- Card, FeatureCard (from ui/card.tsx)
- Collapsible, CollapsibleCard, CollapsibleSection (from ui/collapsible.tsx)
- CopyButton, ReferenceCopyButton (from ui/copy-button.tsx)
- Badge, Button, Tabs (standard UI kit)
- Motion via framer-motion (consistent animation language)

The tutorial components should **wrap and compose** these, not duplicate.

---

# Deliverables

## 1. TutorialProgress Component
**File**: components/tutorial/TutorialProgress.tsx

**Functionality**:
- Vertical step list on desktop (left sidebar)
- Horizontal progress bar on mobile
- Current step highlighted with accent color
- Completed steps show checkmark
- Clickable steps for navigation (with completion gate option)
- Displays total time remaining estimate

**Props**:
\`\`\`typescript
interface TutorialProgressProps {
  steps: TutorialStepMeta[];
  currentStep: number;
  completedSteps: number[];
  onStepClick?: (stepIndex: number) => void;
  allowJumpAhead?: boolean; // Default false
}
\`\`\`

**Design**: Use existing accent colors, animate with framer-motion

---

## 2. TutorialStep Component
**File**: components/tutorial/TutorialStep.tsx

**Functionality**:
- Step number + title header
- Time estimate badge (e.g., "~5 min")
- "What you'll learn" bullet list (collapsed by default on mobile)
- "What you'll do" action checklist
- Main content area (accepts children/MDX)
- Collapsible "More details" section
- Collapsible "Troubleshooting" section
- Back/Next navigation footer

**Props**:
\`\`\`typescript
interface TutorialStepProps {
  stepNumber: number;
  totalSteps: number;
  title: string;
  estimatedTime: string;
  whatYouLearn: string[];
  whatYouDo: string[];
  moreDetails?: React.ReactNode;
  troubleshooting?: TroubleshootingItem[];
  onBack: () => void;
  onNext: () => void;
  isFirstStep?: boolean;
  isLastStep?: boolean;
  children: React.ReactNode; // Main content
}
\`\`\`

---

## 3. TutorialCodeBlock Component
**File**: components/tutorial/TutorialCodeBlock.tsx

**Functionality**:
- Syntax highlighting (bash, typescript, markdown, json)
- Copy button with success feedback (reuse CopyButton)
- Optional title bar with filename/description
- Optional line numbers
- Collapsible for long code blocks
- "Diff" mode for before/after examples

**Props**:
\`\`\`typescript
interface TutorialCodeBlockProps {
  code: string;
  language?: 'bash' | 'typescript' | 'markdown' | 'json' | 'text';
  title?: string;
  description?: string;
  showLineNumbers?: boolean;
  collapsible?: boolean;
  defaultCollapsed?: boolean;
  diff?: { before: string; after: string }; // Alternative to code
}
\`\`\`

**Syntax Highlighting**: Use shiki or prism (check what brennerbot.org already uses)

---

## 4. TutorialTip Component
**File**: components/tutorial/TutorialTip.tsx

**Functionality**:
- Four variants: pro, warning, note, important
- Consistent icon per variant
- Accent color per variant
- Collapsible content for longer tips

**Props**:
\`\`\`typescript
interface TutorialTipProps {
  variant: 'pro' | 'warning' | 'note' | 'important';
  title?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
  collapsible?: boolean;
}
\`\`\`

**Visual Design**:
- pro: green accent, lightbulb icon
- warning: amber accent, warning triangle icon
- note: blue accent, info icon
- important: red accent, exclamation icon

---

## 5. TutorialCheckpoint Component
**File**: components/tutorial/TutorialCheckpoint.tsx

**Functionality**:
- Celebratory visual treatment (subtle animation)
- "You've completed [X]!" header
- List of accomplishments (what they did)
- Preview of what's next
- Continue button

**Props**:
\`\`\`typescript
interface TutorialCheckpointProps {
  title: string;
  accomplishments: string[];
  nextPreview: string;
  onContinue: () => void;
